        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 12 at 1:21PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 116 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking developing thunderstorms
near the Little Belt, Judith and Snowy Mountains with a stronger
thunderstorm 12 miles southwest of Hobson, or 22 miles southeast of
Stanford, moving northeast at 10 mph. Conditions are favorable for
some of these storms to intensify this afternoon with a few storms
having the ability to produce hail up to one half in in diameter,
brief heavy rainfall and wind gusts to 40 mph in addition to
lightning.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lewistown, Stanford, Denton, Hobson, Winifred, Moore, Grass Range,
Geyser, Roy, Fergus, Windham, Forestgrove, Utica, Danvers, Valentine,
Hilger, Buffalo, Moccasin, Ackley Lake State Park, and Glengarry.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

These storms may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional
information and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
